em>=E2=80=9D Never mind the accounting for the money or how it went missing=
; the most obvious problem here is that FTX couldn=E2=80=99t open a bank ac=
count and so used Alameda as a way to get around the banking system. You ca=
n=E2=80=99t trick banks! That=E2=80=99s bank fraud! That=E2=80=99s an indep=
endent reason to get in very bad trouble! Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s defense h=
ere is like =E2=80=9Coh no we weren=E2=80=99t intentionally stealing money =
from our customers; we just accidentally misplaced their money because we w=
ere=C2=A0doing bank fraud.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s not helpful!</p>
